Timetable of Class Meetings

PLEASE NOTE: Banner functions, including the Timetable of Class Meetings, are now compatible with Chrome and Safari.

Note on updates to the Timetable -- It is important to check the Timetable, rather than the ORC/Catalog to confirm the latest information about a course, including the meeting time, instructor, and distributive and/or world culture designation associated with a course.

 

The distributive column on the Timetable is important since it contains the most up-to-date information on the distributive and/or world culture designation for the course. In some cases, the instructor has submitted a request to the Committee on Instruction for a change or addition in the distributive or world culture designation for a course since the ORC/Catalog was published.

 

Click on the subject code link below to view department/program requirements from the ORC/Catalog for that subject.

 

To view textbook requirements information as entered by the department/program at the time of course election click on the icon in the Text column.

 

To view learning objectives information as entered by the department/program at the time of course election, click the icon under the Lrn Obj column.

 

To view a course description click on the Course Title.

 

Please check with the department/program for any updates.
